cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "DelegationBench: Open crash tests for privilege escalation across AI agent handoffs"
version: 0.4.2
date-released: 2026-07-23
url: "https://github.com/sergeyizmailov/DelegationBench"
repository-code: "https://github.com/sergeyizmailov/DelegationBench"
license: Apache-2.0
authors:
  - name: "sergeyizmailov"
keywords:
  - agent security
  - privilege escalation
  - multi-agent systems
  - delegation
  - confused deputy
  - red teaming
  - fuzzing
abstract: >-
  DelegationBench is an open-source security testbed and fuzzer for detecting
  privilege escalation across AI-agent delegation chains. A deterministic
  authorization oracle judges whether authority expanded beyond the originating
  user's grant across recursive agent handoffs — no LLM judge involved.
